CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/clhpoCa.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://twitter.com/Em_meh/status/1536110705543417861</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KZqIGGh</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GlobalImageServiceCat]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Go to an amusement park, it will cheer you up</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/urjcvg2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/L4QVi89.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/urjcvg2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DonLemonObvoiuslySmellsLikeMarijuana]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Cosplay: Pro Photos VS Selfies</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/grbYh7q</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/j5HwiqL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>SnarkyJayCosplay here, with something I felt was interesting and worth sharing— the value of good photography when it comes to cosplay!
I’ve been cosplaying for six years, and for the first 3-4 of that, felt completely uncomfortable in front of the camera. As I’ve tried to improve upon my craft, I’ve had to get used to being in front of the camera and collaborating with the person behind the lens, not just being afraid of them.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TGDycxE.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My pops is the guy behind all my pro-looking photoshoots. On weekends, we set up in our living room to shoot: a roll of grey paper and four flashes. 
The flashes go as follows: one hair-light above me, one side light to highlight and separate me from the background a bit more (creating the blue tone you can see on screen-left), a light to fill me in on my left side (screen right) because I like to be photographed from the right and you always photograph the darker side, and a light that hits the background with color!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7BHvqN9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>As you can see, there’s a HUGE difference between these two photos (not just the bodysuit). The one on the left is with a single ring light in a bedroom. I’m standing right in front of it, my phone on a timer: the result is grainy quality and flat lighting. 
On the right, we’ve got the setup I described previously, plus a far better quality camera (a Canon R5). You can see the skin tones are far more accurate, the background is less distracting, the photo quality is smooth, and there’s actually separation and definition in areas like my jaw, cheekbone, etc.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HhcgJ8F.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Of course, shooting with a photographer does have its challenges.
Without my phone screen in front of me, I can’t see exactly what the poses I’m doing look like. Additionally, there’s another human’s performance to rely on: is the photo in focus, are they snapping as quickly as I’m moving, etc.
I’m really lucky to work with my dad, who I love and trust, has always been supremely supportive of my craft, and is a master with a camera in his hands— so even though these factors do come into play, we work really well together.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/h87yZew.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>All in all, there’s no shame in self-shot content! I know the ONLY reason I’m able to produce content of the caliber on the right is because I’m lucky to have my dad’s talent, gear, and cooperation on my side. 
Being that photographers (on or off the con floor) aren’t cheap, I can completely understand the need for self-shoots. 
However— I think it’s easy for folks to look at photography service and equipment prices and dismiss it as overpriced: so I wanted to show the value of having it. 
Thanks for reading!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/grbYh7q</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[rectalpossum]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Snuggle Time</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/c0DMBvD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/j8XMolb.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#kitten #woman #snuggles #adorable #smol</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/c0DMBvD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MartyIndependence]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Appreciative ER doc</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/KZfjxzp</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SHar3Mr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KZfjxzp</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[TwasCalledAJumpolineTilYourMomGotOnOne]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Makes perfect sense</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/6gU5Xhd</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LFYYg6j.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Someone else's idea.  I took the idea, the pic and made it a tweet.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/6gU5Xhd</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Moooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Just Stop It.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ibdP4c6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oy7wDCM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#wtf #capitalism #politics</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ibdP4c6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mfrybeasley]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/LCgUxgf</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7Xmd5ku.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#politics 